lines.text: 'Calculation of Salem payout: Actual market share was 70% above market-share level required for payout of $31.25. Difference
between $31.25 payout and $62.50 payout is $31.25. 70% of $31.25 = $21.88. Adding $21.88 to $31.25 payout level = $53.13
Calculation of Doral payout: Actual market share was 60% above market-share level required for payout of $31.25. Difference
between $31.25 payout and $62.50 payout is $31.25. 60% of $31.25 = $18.75. Adding $18.75 to $31.25 payout level = $50.00
Net Income: Net Income is defined as operating earnings minus amortization of trade-
marks and goodwill, interest and taxes
Eligible Employees: The award is paid to regular full-time employees participating in A.J.
Reynolds Tobacco's General Employee Bonus Plan (GEBP) and who are not in the
management Annual incentive Awards Plan (AlAP) or the Sales Incentive Awards Plan
(SIAP). RJR Packaging employees receive 60% of the GEBP award plus an additional
component that relates to RJR Packaging's return on assets, which is communicated
Withholdings: The award will be subject to tax withholdings as well as applicable Capital
